caption: SUPPORT SMALL BUSINESS 😊Delicious, fast, and friendly place! Great breakfast brought out piping hot, with super large portions. I loved the flavors a lot. I went to this little Cuban cafe nearly everyday when I worked downtown. This place has great cafe con leche at a great price, great breakfast sandwiches on Cuban bread, and delicious sweet treats such as the cinnamon and cheese bread. This place was always very busy at lunch time prior to COVID but the service was always pretty quick for how busy it was.

I hope this was a one time occurrence but I will definitely not go there again. I ordered a pressed cuban sandwich and what I got was really gross. Loaded with mustard and pickles, I'm guessing it was microwaved then pressed because parts of the bread was chewy and others were hard as a rock. One or two slices of ham, two slices of salami and chunks of pork. The worst part was that something in there smelled and tasted unusual so when I decided to take it apart, I had to dig the salami off of the bread with my nails. Needless to say I didn't finish the sandwich. Then to top it off, I also bought chips... and of course they would be stale. Smh
